=========================================
C++14 LAMBDA INIT CAPTURE (MOVE CAPTURE)
INTERVIEW NOTES
=========================================

1. What is Lambda Init Capture?

Lambda Init Capture is a C++14 feature that allows a lambda to create its own captured variable and initialize it using any expression.

Syntax

[captured_variable = expression]

Example

[p = std::move(ptr)]

Before C++14, lambdas could only capture existing variables by value or reference. 
Since std::unique_ptr cannot be copied, it couldn't be captured by value.
Lambda Init Capture solves this by allowing ownership to be moved into the lambda.

-----------------------------------------

2. Why was it introduced?

Before C++14, lambdas could only capture existing variables.

Example

auto ptr = make_unique<int>(100);

auto f = [ptr]()
{
    cout << *ptr;
};

This DOES NOT compile because:

• unique_ptr cannot be copied.
• [ptr] performs capture by value (copy).

-----------------------------------------

3. C++14 Solution

auto ptr = make_unique<int>(100);

auto f = [p = move(ptr)]()
{
    cout << *p;
};

f();

Output

100

